# How to run the backend server 
1. Make sure you have Node.js and npm installed on your machine.
2. Navigate to the backend directory in your terminal.
3. Install the required dependencies by running:
   ```
   npm install
   ```
4. Start the server by running:
   ```
   npm run dev
   ```
5. The server should now be running on http://localhost:3000 (or the port specified in your environment variables).
6. You can test the API endpoints on the swagger documentation at http://localhost:3000/docs/

# .env file configuration
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/software_architecture
PORT=3000

